Name: MSPT System Design

Items.StringList: Heat to cycle (original)|Net system electricity output

Caption.String: The heliostat field layout does not automatically update when you change the design (for example, the solar multiple). We assume a field optical efficiency of 60% to estimate the solar multiple and thermal power achievable with the current field layout. If these estimated values are significantly different than the corresponding values in the Tower and Receiver section below, you may want to generate a new field layout. On the Heliostat Field page, you have options to generate a new layout from the user interface or generate a new layout when you run the model.

The design point parameters determine the nominal ratings of each part of the power tower system. After specifying the design point parameters here, you can specify details of each component of the system on the Heliostat Field, Tower and Receiver, Thermal Storage, and Power Cycle input pages.
